Game-rules content
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

dndwright's rules tables (hit dice, spellcasting progression / spell slots,
armor base AC, save proficiencies, class spellcasting abilities, etc.) encode
game *mechanics* — facts about how D&D 5e (2024) characters are computed. Where
those facts come from published game content, they derive from the:

    Dungeons & Dragons System Reference Document 5.2.1 (SRD 5.2)
    English edition, published May 1, 2025.
    © Wizards of the Coast LLC, licensed under
    Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY-4.0).
    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

    Source document:
    https://media.dndbeyond.com/compendium-images/srd/5.2/SRD_CC_v5.2.1.pdf

Bundled content (dndwright.content): the magic_items, conditions, feats, species,
spells, classes, backgrounds, weapons, armor, and creatures (the Monsters A–Z
bestiary) catalogs are derived from the SRD 5.2 (CC-BY-4.0, attributed above) —
see each file's metadata. (The content generator produces original homebrew, not
derived from any copyrighted source.)

